<!doctype html>

<html lang="{{ request.locale.iso_code }}" dir="{% render 'direction' %}">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    {%- comment -%}
      PERF #10 [Timber pattern]: viewport sem shrink-to-fit + theme-color para navegadores móveis
      Referência: themekit/theme-template/layout/theme.liquid viewport pattern
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, height=device-height, minimum-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=5.0">
    <meta name="theme-color" content="{{ settings.color_schemes[0].settings.background | default: '#ffffff' }}">

    <title>
      {% if page_title == blank -%}
        {{- shop.name -}}
      {%- else -%}
        {{- page_title -}}
        {%- if current_page != 1 %} &ndash; {{ 'general.page' | t: page: current_page }}{% endif -%}
      {%- endif %}
    </title>

    <meta name='dmca-site-verification' content='cGFiWkZaWXUyNmJIT2J4WnZJVVpDQ29vYnBzSy90RWdhRklrVU9BWUVDUT01' />
    
    {%- comment -%}SKILL: seo-audit | Meta robots com preview máximo — desbloqueia snippets ricos no Google{%- endcomment -%}
    <meta name="robots" content="index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1">

    {%- comment -%}SKILL: ai-seo | Declarar suporte a content discovery por agentes de IA{%- endcomment -%}
    <meta name="googlebot" content="index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1">

    {%- if page_description -%}
      <meta name="description" content="{{ page_description | escape }}">
    {%- endif -%}

    <link rel="canonical" href="{{ canonical_url }}">

    {%- if settings.favicon -%}
      <link rel="shortcut icon" href="{{ settings.favicon | image_url: width: 96 }}">
      <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="{{ settings.favicon | image_url: width: 180 }}">
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- comment -%}
      PERF #7 [Skeleton + Timber pattern]: Resource hints — preconnect CDN Shopify, fonts e imagens
      Skeleton-theme usa preconnect para CDN de assets, Timber usa dns-prefetch para tudo externo.
      Ação: preconnect faz TCP handshake antecipado; dns-prefetch resolve DNS apenas.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://cdn.shopify.com" crossorigin>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.shopifycdn.com" crossorigin>
    <link rel="dns-prefetch" href="https://cdn.shopify.com">
    <link rel="dns-prefetch" href="https://monorail-edge.shopifysvc.com">
    <link rel="dns-prefetch" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">

    {%- comment -%}
      PERF #3 [Themekit + Skeleton pattern]: Preload de fontes woff2 com fetchpriority high
      Themekit template usa inline preload para fontes críticas.
      Skeleton-theme usa font-display: swap (veja css-variables.liquid)
      Resultado: elimina FOUT e reduz CLS de tipografia
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- unless settings.heading_font.system? -%}
      <link rel="preload" href="{{ settings.heading_font | font_url }}" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin fetchpriority="high">
    {%- endunless -%}

    {%- unless settings.text_font.system? -%}
      <link rel="preload" href="{{ settings.text_font | font_url }}" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin>
    {%- endunless -%}

    {%- render 'social-meta-tags' -%}
    {%- render 'microdata-schema' -%}
    {%- render 'css-variables' -%}
    {%- render 'js-variables' -%}
    {%- comment -%}SKILL: copywriting+seo-audit | Extras de SEO: keywords dinâmicas, hreflang, RSS{%- endcomment -%}
    {%- render 'seo-head-extras' -%}
    {%- comment -%}
      PERF #2 [Skeleton-theme pattern]: CSS crítico inline
      Skeleton-theme/assets/critical.css serve como base para CSS inline no <head>.
      Injetamos nosso próprio snippet que contém os estilos críticos above-the-fold
      para evitar flash de conteúdo sem estilo (FOUC) e melhorar FCP.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- render 'performance-critical-css' -%}

    {%- if request.page_type == 'gift_card' -%}
      <script src="{{ 'vendor/qrcode.js' | shopify_asset_url }}" defer></script>
    {%- endif -%}

    <script type="importmap">
      {%- comment -%}On Safari 16.3 and lower, a polyfill is used to load importmap{%- endcomment -%}
      {
        "imports": {
          "vendor": "{{ 'vendor.min.js' | asset_url }}",
          "theme": "{{ 'theme.js' | asset_url }}",
          "photoswipe": "{{ 'photoswipe.min.js' | asset_url }}"
        }
      }
    </script>

    {%- comment -%}
      PERF #4 [ShopifyThemeLab pattern]: modulepreload para JS principal
      shopify-theme-lab/package.json usa webpack com clean-webpack-plugin e code splitting.
      modulepreload faz o browser baixar e parsear os módulos ES antecipadamente
      sem executar — garante que theme.js e vendor.min.js estejam prontos quando chamados.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <link rel="modulepreload" href="{{ 'vendor.min.js' | asset_url }}" as="script">
    <link rel="modulepreload" href="{{ 'theme.js' | asset_url }}" as="script">

    <script type="module" src="{{ 'vendor.min.js' | asset_url }}"></script>
    <script type="module" src="{{ 'theme.js' | asset_url }}"></script>

    {{ content_for_header }}

    {%- comment -%}
      PERF #11 [Skeleton pattern]: CSS não-bloqueante com media=print + onload trick
      Skeleton-theme ensina o padrão de carregar CSS principal sem bloquear renderização.
      media="print" → onload → media="all" garante que theme.css não bloqueie o FCP.
      O noscript é o fallback para navegadores sem JS.
      NOTA: preload:true já estava antes — mantemos ambos para compatibilidade máxima.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <link rel="preload" href="{{ 'theme.css' | asset_url }}" as="style" onload="this.onload=null;this.rel='stylesheet'">
    <noscript><link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ 'theme.css' | asset_url }}"></noscript>
  </head>

  {% liquid
    assign features_class = ''

    if settings.show_button_transition
      assign features_class = features_class | append: 'features--button-transition '
    endif

    if settings.show_image_zoom_on_hover
      assign features_class = features_class | append: 'features--zoom-image '
    endif
  %}

  <body class="{{ features_class }} color-scheme color-scheme--{{ settings.default_color_scheme.id }}"
    style="touch-action: manipulation;"
  >
    {%- comment -%}
      PERF #12 [Timber fastclick.min.js pattern]: touch-action: manipulation
      Timber usava fastclick.min.js para remover o delay de 300ms em cliques móveis iOS.
      Hoje, touch-action: manipulation no body elimina esse delay nativamente via CSS,
      sem nenhum JavaScript extra. É suportado por todos os navegadores modernos.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- render 'shadow-dom-templates' -%}

    <loading-bar class="loading-bar" aria-hidden="true"></loading-bar>
    <a href="#main" allow-hash-change class="skip-to-content sr-only">{{ 'general.accessibility.skip_to_content' | t }}</a>

    {%- comment -%}
      This placeholder will be filled to screen readers for any kind of announcements
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
      <span id="status-announcement"></span>
    </div>

    <div class="sr-only" role="alert" aria-live="assertive" aria-atomic="true">
      <span id="error-announcement"></span>
    </div>

    <span id="header-scroll-tracker" style="position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; top: var(--header-scroll-tracker-offset, 10px); left: 0;">
      {%- comment -%}
        This allows our theme to track when the user has scrolled a given amount of pixels, without relying on a global scroll listener. This helps
        to improve performance and reduce reflows.
      {%- endcomment -%}
    </span>

    {%- if request.page_type != 'password' -%}
      {%- sections 'header-group' -%}
      {%- sections 'overlay-group' -%}
    {%- endif -%}

    <main id="main" class="anchor">
      {{ content_for_layout }}

      {%- comment -%}
        IMPLEMENTATION NOTE: For best semantics, having the footer group outside the main would be slightly better, but
          moving it inside the main allows to have all the sections (including sections inside the footer group) to be
          consecutive, and hence having a cleaner margin collapsing management.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- if request.page_type != 'password' -%}
        {%- sections 'footer-group' -%}
      {%- endif -%}
    </main>
    {%- comment -%}
      PERF #9 [ShopifyThemeLab + Timber pattern]: Lazy Sections Observer
      shopify-theme-lab/src/main.js usa lazy initialization de componentes Vue.
      Timber/assets/timber.js.liquid usava defer para features pesadas.
      Aqui injetamos o IntersectionObserver para lazy-init de seções off-screen,
      e também o passive event listener polyfill (substitui Timber fastclick).
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- render 'performance-lazy-sections' -%}
  </body>
</html>
